{{define "pages/docs.gohtml"}}
<div>
  <h1>📖 Documentation</h1>
  <p>Learn how to use Lintasan for AI model routing and management.</p>

  <div>
    <!-- Sidebar nav -->
    <nav>
      <div class="card">
        <a href="#getting-started">Getting Started</a>
        <a href="#configuration">Configuration</a>
        <a href="#api-reference">API Reference</a>
        <a href="#routing">Routing</a>
        <a href="#fallback">Fallback Chains</a>
        <a href="#caching">Caching</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div>
      <section id="getting-started" class="card mb-4">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <p>Lintasan is a lightweight AI model gateway that routes requests across multiple providers. It supports OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, Groq, Ollama, and any OpenAI-compatible endpoint.</p>
        <h3>Quick Start</h3>
        <pre><code># Set your master key
export LINTASAN_MASTER_KEY="your-secret-key"

# Run the server
./lintasan-go

# Access dashboard at http://localhost:8080/dashboard</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section id="configuration" class="card mb-4">
        <h2>Configuration</h2>
        <p>All configuration is done through the dashboard UI. No config files needed. Settings are stored in SQLite and persist across restarts.</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Master Key:</strong> Protects your dashboard and API.</li>
          <li><strong>Cache TTL:</strong> How long responses are cached.</li>
          <li><strong>Rate Limits:</strong> Per-key and per-model limits.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="api-reference" class="card mb-4">
        <h2>API Reference</h2>
        <p>Lintasan exposes an OpenAI-compatible API at <code>/v1/chat/completions</code>. Use your API key in the <code>Authorization: Bearer</code> header.</p>
        <pre><code>curl http://localhost:8080/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"model":"gpt-4o","messages":[{"role":"user","content":"Hello"}]}'</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section id="routing" class="card mb-4">
        <h2>Routing</h2>
        <p>Configure routing priorities to control which provider handles requests for each model. Higher priority providers are tried first. Use the Routing page to drag and drop provider order.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="fallback" class="card mb-4">
        <h2>Fallback Chains</h2>
        <p>Fallback chains define a sequence of providers to try when the primary provider fails. Create chains that step through providers in order until one succeeds.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="caching" class="card mb-4">
        <h2>Caching</h2>
        <p>Lintasan can cache LLM responses to reduce costs and latency. Configure cache behavior in Settings. Cached responses are served instantly without calling upstream providers.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
{{end}}
